quick wins: urban dictionary, modifier-key gate, discovery toast, onboarding

- Urban Dictionary as the final fallback for slang and neologisms when every
  formal source returns nothing. Filters out brand-new troll defs by requiring
  a minimum thumbs total before ranking by net score.
- Trigger modifier setting (Off / Alt / Ctrl / Shift). When set, dblclick only
  fires the lookup if the modifier is held — cuts accidental triggers from
  the muscle memory of double-clicking to select.
- One-time Ctrl+K discoverability toast on pages with >=800 words of article
  text. Lives in its own shadow root, auto-dismisses after 10s, flagged
  permanently after first dismissal.
- Onboarding modal refresh: leads with "Works out of the box" and explicitly
  frames the AI key as optional polish, not a requirement.
